The Peoples Democratic Party’s National Working Committee has announced that it will present a certificate of return to the party’s presidential candidate, Abubakar Atiku. After receiving 371 votes, Atiku was elected as the party’s presidential candidate during a special national convention held in Abuja on May 28 and 29, 2022. Also Read: Atiku Emerges PDP’s 2023 Presidential Flagbearer According to the party’s national publicity secretary, Debo Ologunagba, all governors, governorship candidates, presidential aspirants, members of the Board of Trustees, members of the National Assembly, other party candidates, and all critical stakeholders are expected to attend the special ceremony. The statement further said the event would hold on Wednesday, June 1, 2022, by noon at the PDP National Secretariat, Abuja.